%% Routing Flow — ModelRouter Core Pipeline
flowchart TD
    Start([InferenceRequest received]) --> Cache{Cache hit?}
    Cache -- yes --> ReturnCached[Return cached response]
    Cache -- no --> Policy[Resolve effective RoutingPolicy<br/>system → tenant → request]

    Policy --> Enum[Enumerate eligible candidates<br/>capability match, not excluded]
    Enum --> Eligible{Any eligible<br/>candidates?}
    Eligible -- no --> ErrUnsat[Error: POLICY_UNSATISFIABLE]

    Eligible -- yes --> Score[Attach live scores<br/>latency · error rate · cost · capacity]
    Score --> Strategy[RoutingStrategy.rank<br/>e.g. cheapest-viable, lowest-latency, AI-powered]
    Strategy --> Ranked[Ranked candidate list]

    Ranked --> Invoke[Invoke top candidate via adapter]
    Invoke --> Outcome{Outcome?}

    Outcome -- success --> Normalize[Normalize response]
    Normalize --> WriteCache[Write-through cache]
    WriteCache --> EmitEvents[Emit usage/cost events → Kafka async]
    EmitEvents --> Return([Return response to client])

    Outcome -- retryable failure<br/>pre-first-byte --> RetryCheck{Retry budget<br/>remaining?}
    RetryCheck -- yes --> Backoff[Apply backoff] --> Invoke
    RetryCheck -- no --> NextCandidate{Next candidate<br/>in ranked list?}

    Outcome -- non-retryable failure --> NextCandidate
    NextCandidate -- yes --> Invoke
    NextCandidate -- no --> ErrExhausted[Error: ALL_CANDIDATES_EXHAUSTED]

    ErrUnsat --> ReturnErr([Return error to client])
    ErrExhausted --> ReturnErr
